    "Li et al. (2021) argue that their modifications avoid the quadratic computation of self-attention, its memory bottleneck in stacking layers for long inputs, and the speed plunge in predicting long outputs.",
    "The work in Ye et al. (2020) intends to better learn the long and short dependencies among longitudinal data.",
    "Thus, it uses two components, which are a traditional transformer and a 1-dimensional convolutional layer.",
    "The work in Dong et al. (2021) relies on graphs as input.",
    "Thus, the specialization of its final prediction layer is a natural design step for the learning process."
